  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 350 degrees F.",
    "Heat olive oil in a kadhai over medium heat, add onions and garlic, cook until translucent.",
    "Add carrots and continue cooking for about 10 minutes.",
    "Stir in pomegranate molasses and salt. Simmer for another minute.",
    "Carefully place vine leaves on top of the vegetables, ensuring they're fully coated with the sauce.",
    "Fold or roll the vine leaves to form a pakode-like shape, place them inside the kadhai.",
    "Bake in preheated oven for 20-25 minutes until golden brown and crisp.",
    "Serve hot as a low-glycemic-friendly side dish."
